body:
@mermoldy Thank you for your contribution! Sorry that this dropped out of the radar.

When this [feature was first introduced by @ViktorOgnev](https://github.com/apache/libcloud/pull/729/files), no tests were added, and I would like to fix this this time. Could you add a test with a fixture that tests that encryption works with both `ex_encrypted` and `ex_kms_key_id`?

Thank you!

@lmorfitt I'm really sorry that we took this long to get back to you.

In April 2017 we released libcloud 2.0 that drops the dependency on httplib. We now use `requests` and as a result no longer set `skip_host` and `skip_accept_encoding`.

Unfortunately I don't have an Azure account so I can't check myself. Can you please tell us if that fixed your issue? Thanks!

@r2ronoha Thanks! We're nearly there.

Is the description expected to appear in the response when you're using the real EC2 service? Ideally, the test should ensure that the description was actually taken into account, possibly using fake EC2 requests (test fixtures).

Oh, and the lint does not pass, see https://travis-ci.org/apache/libcloud/jobs/283747844 which says "libcloud/compute/drivers/ec2.py:7454:27: E128 continuation line under-indented for visual indent".
